Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all
produce.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add @shredded carrots{4%ounce}, @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce},
and a pinch of @salt{}; cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are wilted
and softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, quarter @lime{1}.

Stir @shelled edamame{4%ounce}, @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, and
@sweet Thai chili sauce{2%ounce} into pan with veggies. Bring to a simmer,
then reduce heat to medium low.

Once water is boiling, add @ramen noodles{6%ounce} to pot. Cook until
tender, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Drain and rinse thoroughly under cold water, at least ~{30%seconds}.

> This stops cooking and helps prevent sticky noodles.

Add drained noodles to pan with sauce and veggies; toss until combined and
noodles are warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}. (TIP: If sauce is too thick, add
a splash of water.) Stir in a big squeeze of lime juice to taste; season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide between #bowls{}. Roughly tear @cilantro{¼%ounce}(leaves, stems discarded),
and sprinkle over noodles. Top with @peanuts{1%ounce} and serve with any
remaining lime wedges on the side.